# Project Guidelines for Seafood Calculator

## Security
- Never read or modify .env files directly
- Keep credentials out of logs
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper authentication
- Sanitize all user inputs

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new features
- Follow error handling in utils/errors.ts
- Implement proper type checking
- Use async/await over promises
- Follow React hooks best practices

## Documentation
- Update docs when modifying features
- Keep README.md in sync
- Document all API endpoints
- Use JSDoc comments for functions
- Create ADRs for major decisions

## Testing
- Maintain 80% test coverage
- Unit test all calculations
- Integration test API endpoints
- E2E test critical flows
- Performance test shipping calculator